22/06/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The main opposition Republican People's Party (CHP) is pledging to fight terrorism, protect the secular nature of the Turkish Republic, boost economic development and abolish university entrance exams, if it comes to power after the July 22nd parliamentary elections. CHP leader Deniz Baykal presented the party's programme at a news conference late on Wednesday (June 20th), kicking off the campaign. To fight terrorism, Baykal said Turkey should continue combating all sources, both inside and outside the country. (NTV, Aksam - 21/06/07)
